Name: access_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Access procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of Access requests.

Name: access_error
Desc: Number of erroneous Access procedure requests. The Access procedure determines the access rights that a user has with respect to a file system object.

Name: access_total
Desc: Total number of Access procedure requests. It is the total number of access success and access error requests.

Name: commit_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Commit procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of Commit requests.

Name: commit_error
Desc: Number of erroneous Commit procedure requests. The Commit procedure forces or flushes data to stable storage that was previously written with a Write procedure call with stable field set to UNSTABLE.

Name: commit_total
Desc: Total number of Commit procedure requests. It is the total number of Commit success and Commit error requests.

Name: create_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Create procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of Create requests.

Name: create_error
Desc: Number of erroneous Create procedure requests. The Create procedure creates a regular file.

Name: create_total
Desc: Total number Create of procedure requests. It is the total number of create success and create error requests.

Name: fsinfo_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of FSInfo procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of FSInfo requests.

Name: fsinfo_error
Desc: Number of erroneous FsInfo procedure requests. The FsInfo procedure retrieves nonvolatile file system state information and provides general information about the NFS version 3 protocol server implementation

Name: fsinfo_total
Desc: Total number FSInfo of procedure requests. It is the total number of FSInfo success and FSInfo error requests.

Name: fsstat_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of FSStat procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of FSStat requests.

Name: fsstat_error
Desc: Number of erroneous FsStat procedure requests. The FsStat procedure retrieves volatile file system state information.

Name: fsstat_total
Desc: Total number FSStat of procedure requests. It is the total number of FSStat success and FSStat error requests.

Name: getattr_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of GetAttr procedure requests. This counter keeps track of the average response time of GetAttr requests.

Name: getattr_error
Desc: Number of erroneous GetAttr procedure requests. The GetAttr procedure retrieves the attributes for a specified file system object.

Name: getattr_total
Desc: Total number of Getattr procedure requests. It is the total number of getattr success and getattr error requests.

Name: link_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Link procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of Link requests.

Name: link_error
Desc: Number of erroneous Link procedure requests. The Link procedure creates a hard link. A hard link is a directory entry that associates a name with a file on a file system.

Name: link_total
Desc: Total number Link of procedure requests. It is the total number of Link success and Link error requests.

Name: lookup_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of LookUp procedure requests. This shows the average time it takes for the LookUp operation to reply to the request.

Name: lookup_error
Desc: Number of erroneous LookUp procedure requests. The LookUp procedure searches a directory for a specific name and returns the file handle for the corresponding file system object.

Name: lookup_total
Desc: Total number of Lookup procedure requests. It is the total number of lookup success and lookup error requests.

Name: mkdir_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of MkDir procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of MkDir requests.

Name: mkdir_error
Desc: Number of erroneous MkDir procedure requests. The MkDir procedure creates a new subdirectory.

Name: mkdir_total
Desc: Total number MkDir of procedure requests. It is the total number of MkDir success and MkDir error requests.

Name: mknod_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of MkNod procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of MkNod requests.

Name: mknod_error
Desc: Number of erroneous MkNod procedure requests. The MkNod procedure creates a special file that can be device files or named pipes.

Name: mknod_total
Desc: Total number MkNod of procedure requests. It is the total number of MkNod success and MkNod error requests.

Name: nfsv3_ops
Desc: Total number of NFSv3 procedure requests per second.

Name: nfsv3_read_ops

Name: nfsv3_write_ops
Desc: Total observed NFSv3 write operations per second.

Name: null_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Null procedure requests.

Name: null_error
Desc: Number of erroneous Null procedure requests. A null procedure does nothing. It is used for testing and timing.

Name: null_total
Desc: Total number of Null procedure requests. It is the total of null success and null error requests.

Name: pathconf_avg_latency

Name: pathconf_error

Name: pathconf_total
Desc: Total number PathConf of procedure requests. It is the total number of PathConf success and PathConf error requests.

Name: raidprop_error

Name: readdirplus_total
Desc: Total number ReadDirPlus of procedure requests. It is the total number of ReadDirPlus success and ReadDirPlus error requests.

Name: remove_avg_latency

Desc: Number of erroneous PathConf procedure requests. The PathConf retrieves the pathconf information for a file or directory.

Name: pathconf_total
Desc: Total number PathConf of procedure requests. It is the total number of PathConf success and PathConf error requests.

Name: raidprop_error
Desc: Number of times RAID errors encountered in NFSv3 path.

Name: read_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Read procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of Read requests.

Name: read_error
Desc: Number of erroneous Read procedure requests. The Read procesure reads data from a file.

Name: read_symlink_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of ReadSymLink procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of ReadSymLink requests.

Name: read_symlink_error
Desc: Number of erroneous ReadSymlink procedure requests. The ReadSymLink procedure reads the data associated with a symbolic link. A symbolic link is a file system object that points to another file system object.

Name: read_symlink_total
Desc: Total number of ReadSymLink procedure requests. It is the total number of read symlink success and read symlink error requests.

Name: read_total
Desc: Total number Read of procedure requests. It is the total number of read success and read error requests.

Name: readdir_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of ReadDir procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of ReadDir requests.

Name: readdir_error
Desc: Number of erroneous ReadDir procedure requests. The ReadDir retrieves a variable number of entries from a directory and returns the name of file identifier for each.

Name: readdir_postop_error
Desc: Number of failed Postop ReadDir procedures. Postop ReadDir errors are failures in the response of the request.

Name: readdir_total
Desc: Total number ReadDir of procedure requests. It is the total number of ReadDir success and ReadDir error requests.

Name: readdirplus_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of ReadDirPlus procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of ReadDirPlus requests.

Name: readdirplus_error
Desc: Number of erroneous ReadDirPlus procedure requests. The ReadDirPlus retrieves a variable number of entries from a file systesm directory and returns complete information about each.

Name: readdirplus_postop_error
Desc: Number of failed Postop ReadDirPlus procedures. Postop ReadDirPlus errors are failures in the response of the request.

Name: readdirplus_total
Desc: Total number ReadDirPlus of procedure requests. It is the total number of ReadDirPlus success and ReadDirPlus error requests.

Name: remove_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Remove procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of Remove requests.

Name: remove_error
Desc: Number of erroneous Remove procedure requests. The Remove procedure deletes an entry from a directory.

Name: remove_total
Desc: Total number Remove of procedure requests. It is the total number of Remove success and Remove error requests.

Name: rename_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Rename procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of Rename requests.

Name: rename_error
Desc: Number of erroneous Rename procedure requests. The Rename procedure renames the file.

Name: rename_total
Desc: Total number Rename of procedure requests. It is the total number of Rename success and Rename error requests.

Name: rmdir_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of RmDir procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of RmDir requests.

Name: rmdir_error
Desc: Number of erroneous RmDir procedure requests. The RmDir procedure deletes a subdirectory from a directory.

Name: rmdir_total
Desc: Total number RmDir of procedure requests. It is the total number of RmDir success and RmDir error requests.

Name: setattr_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of SetAttr procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of SetAttr requests.

Name: setattr_error
Desc: Number of erroneous SetAttr procedure requests. The SetAttr procedure changes one or more of the attributes of a file system object on the server.

Name: setattr_total
Desc: Total number of Setattr procedure requests. It is the total number of Setattr success and setattr error requests.

Name: symlink_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of SymLink procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of SymLink requests.

Name: symlink_error
Desc: Number of erroneous SymLink procedure requests. The SymLink procedure creates a symbolic link. A symbolic link is a file system object that points to another file system object.

Name: write_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Write procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of Write requests.

Name: write_error
Desc: Number of erroneous Write procedure requests. The Write procedure writes data to a file.

Name: write_total
Desc: Total number of Write procedure requests. It is the total numer of write success and write error requests.

Name: access_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Access procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of Access requests.

Name: access_error
Desc: Number of erroneous Access procedure requests. The Access procedure determines the access rights that a user has with respect to a file system object.

Name: access_total
Desc: Total number of Access procedure requests. It is the total number of access success and access error requests.

Name: commit_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Commit procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of Commit requests.

Name: commit_error
Desc: Number of erroneous Commit procedure requests. The Commit procedure forces or flushes data to stable storage that was previously written with a Write procedure call with stable field set to UNSTABLE.

Name: commit_total
Desc: Total number of Commit procedure requests. It is the total number of Commit success and Commit error requests.

Name: create_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Create procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of Create requests.

Name: create_error
Desc: Number of erroneous Create procedure requests. The Create procedure creates a regular file.

Name: create_total
Desc: Total number Create of procedure requests. It is the total number of create success and create error requests.

Name: fsinfo_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of FSInfo procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of FSInfo requests.

Name: fsinfo_error

Name: fsinfo_total
Desc: Total number FSInfo of procedure requests. It is the total number of FSInfo success and FSInfo error requests.

Name: fsstat_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of FSStat procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of FSStat requests.

Name: fsstat_error

Name: fsstat_total
Desc: Total number FSStat of procedure requests. It is the total number of FSStat success and FSStat error requests.

Name: getattr_avg_latency

Name: getattr_error

Name: getattr_total
Desc: Total number of Getattr procedure requests. It is the total number of getattr success and getattr error requests.

Name: link_avg_latency
Desc: Average latency of Link procedure requests. The counter keeps track of the average response time of Link requests.

Name: lookup_total
Desc: Total number of Lookup procedure requests. It is the total number of lookup success and lookup error requests.

Name: mkdir_total
Desc: Total number MkDir of procedure requests. It is the total number of MkDir success and MkDir error requests.

Desc: Total number MkNod of procedure requests. It is the total number of MkNod success and MkNod error requests.
